  "description": "Thin-film deposition for optical enhancement: MgF₂ anti-reflection coating (quarter-wave, ~100 nm, thermal evaporation at 10⁻⁴ Pa) and aluminum mirror coating (vacuum evaporation, ~100 nm, 88-92% reflectance). Requires vacuum deposition chamber, tungsten/tantalum boats, thickness monitoring. Enables multi-element lens systems and protected mirrors.",
